HEADWORD: Ascertainment
<hw>As`cer*tain"ment</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
ascertaining; a reducing to certainty; a finding out by investigation;
discovery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The positive <qex>ascertainment</qex> of its limits.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

